data.text:
The general election in Newfoundland

has resulted in the party supporting Sir

William Whiteway, the late Premier,

securing a majority of eight votes in the

House of Assembly. '

In July last Sir William Whiteway, the

Speaker, ' Mr. G. H." Emerson, and a

number of other members of the Assembly

were unseated for bribery and

corruption. On the presentation of the

petitions Sir William Whiteway resigned,

and a Ministry was formed by Mr. Good
